VANGERS: One for the Road
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

1. Required libraries:

   - SDL 3.2 or newer
   - SDL_net 3.2 or newer
   - libvorbis
   - SDL3-native clunk from the `sdl3` branch
     (https://github.com/stalkerg/clunk/tree/sdl3)
   - ffmpeg 6.0 or newer
   - toml11 4.4.x
   - zlib

2. Required tools:

   - CMake 4.0 or newer
   - Ninja or make

3. Building:

   $ mkdir build
   $ cd build
   $ cmake ..
   $ make

4. Running:

   $ cd data
   $ ../build/src/vangers


OSX prerequisites

a. Install homebrew
b. brew install sdl3 sdl3_net libvorbis libogg ffmpeg toml11
c. Build/install the `sdl3` branch of clunk
   (https://github.com/stalkerg/clunk/tree/sdl3).
d. Go to 3.


Android integration

The Android host project must provide native SDL3 and SDL3_net CMake packages,
for example through their official Prefab-enabled Android archives, and an
SDL3-native Clunk build. With `ANDROID` enabled this repository builds the
static `vangers` library and exports the standard SDL3 `SDL_main()` entry point
for the host activity's native entry point. The host build must also provide a
toml11 4.4.x CMake package. Save-game files keep their existing binary format.
User preferences migrate once from `options.dat` and `controls.dat` to
`settings.toml`; the legacy files are left unchanged.
